# AWS-DFD-Visualizer custom visualization settings

display.visualizations.custom.AWS-DFD-Visualizer.display_mode = <string>
* Determines the default layout mode (auto or manual).

display.visualizations.custom.AWS-DFD-Visualizer.draggableNodes = <bool>
* Allow users to drag and drop nodes. Default is true.

display.visualizations.custom.AWS-DFD-Visualizer.canZoom = <bool>
* Allow zooming and panning on the diagram. Default is true.

display.visualizations.custom.AWS-DFD-Visualizer.nodeTextSize = <string>
* Size of the node text labels (small, medium, large, extraLarge). Default is medium.

display.visualizations.custom.AWS-DFD-Visualizer.wrapNodeText = <bool>
* Wrap node text to fit within the node boundaries. Default is true.

display.visualizations.custom.AWS-DFD-Visualizer.clusterBy = <string>
* Clustering strategy (none, color, group). Default is none.

display.visualizations.custom.AWS-DFD-Visualizer.defaultNodeType = <string>
* Default shape to use if no specific icon is found. Default is circle.

display.visualizations.custom.AWS-DFD-Visualizer.missingImageURL = <string>
* Absolute or relative URL for a fallback icon if not found.

display.visualizations.custom.AWS-DFD-Visualizer.drilldownClick = <string>
* Valid values are 'single' or 'singleOrDouble'.

display.visualizations.custom.AWS-DFD-Visualizer.enablePhysics = <bool>
* Toggle the D3 force simulation layout calculations on or off.

display.visualizations.custom.AWS-DFD-Visualizer.hideEdgesOnDrag = <bool>
* Temporarily hide edge paths while nodes are being dragged to improve performance.

display.visualizations.custom.AWS-DFD-Visualizer.smoothEdges = <bool>
* Draw curved connections instead of straight lines. Default is true.

display.visualizations.custom.AWS-DFD-Visualizer.linkTextSize = <string>
* Size of the relationship text (small, medium, large, extraLarge). Default is medium.
